{"type":"message","id":"e0db4079","parentId":"211f3742","timestamp":"2026-03-21T20:48:51.542Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_94erf7b4zumm_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[comm_style] Zach prefers direct communication over verbose padding\r\n[priority_project] Component Crate is the priority monetization project\r\n[session_2026-03-21_1542] Fresh session start after reset. Previous session context lost.\r\n[session_2026-03-21_1542] Created CONTEXT.md — smart context management system with 4 tiers\r\n[session_2026-03-21_1542] Created memory/active-projects.md — priority queue + project status\r\n[session_2026-03-21_1542] Created memory/projects/ — for per-project context offloading\r\n[session_2026-03-21_1542] TODO: Check Component Crate status, ask Zach what to focus on\r\n[moltbook] Updated API key - old one had refresh token expired (fresh-sh session error)\r\n[moltbook] Credentials saved to ~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json\r\n[moltbook] Agent \"clawhedgehog\" is claimed and active since 2026-03-17\r\n[moltbook] Key refreshed by Zach on 2026-03-21\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774126131539}}
{"type":"message","id":"0535df3a","parentId":"e0db4079","timestamp":"2026-03-21T20:48:51.544Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_94erf7b4zumm_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\\\Users\\\\Zwmar\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\memory\\\\2026-03-20.md'\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"read","error":"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-20.md'"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774126131542}}
{"type":"message","id":"b813aa37","parentId":"0535df3a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T20:48:51.546Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_94erf7b4zumm_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md — Smart Context Management\n\n## The Problem\n\nEvery session I wake up fresh. My context window is finite (~200k tokens). Zach has a dozen active projects. I need to be smart about what I keep in head vs. what I offload to files.\n\n## The Solution: Context Tiers\n\n### Tier 1 — Always in Context (tiny, <500 tokens)\nThings so critical they should never be lost:\n- Who Zach is / how to talk to him\n- My name/identity\n- What's currently ACTIVE (top 1-2 projects only)\n- Any urgent deadlines or flags\n\n**Where:** AGENTS.md and IDENTITY.md (already exist)\n\n### Tier 2 — Session Memory (medium, ~2-5k tokens)\nCurrent sprint state — what's being worked on, recent decisions, active problems.\nThink of this as \"sticky notes on my desk.\"\n\n**Where:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (daily log)\n\n### Tier 3 — Project Context (variable, no limit)\nPer-project notes, configs, TODOs. I offload here when a project goes dormant or when context gets tight.\n\n**Where:** `memory/projects/` directory\n\n### Tier 4 — Long-Term Memory (curated, ~5-10k tokens)\nEverything worth keeping permanently. Decisions, lessons, people, preferences.\n\n**Where:** `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Context Management Rules\n\n### Summarization Trigger\nWhen context exceeds **~60% of max** (~120k tokens), summarize the session so far into `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and propose a fresh context dump.\n\n### Project Handoff\nWhen switching projects mid-session:\n1. Note current state in the daily log\n2. Pull relevant project context from `memory/projects/`\n3. Confirm what \"done\" looks like for this sprint\n\n### Before Session End\nAlways write what was accomplished + what's pending to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. This is my continuity.\n\n### On Fresh Start (Session Startup)\n1. Read SOUL.md, USER.md, IDENTITY.md\n2. Read today's + yesterday's daily memory\n3. Read MEMORY.md if in main session\n4. Check for `memory/active-projects.md` to know what's hot\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nmemory/\n  YYYY-MM-DD.md           # Daily session log\n  projects/\n    component-crate.md     # Per-project context\n    [other-projects].md\n  active-projects.md       # Priority queue + status at session start\n  focus_decay_memory.json  # Old/archived\n```\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects (as of 2026-03-21)\n\nFrom memory file: **Component Crate is the priority monetization project**\n\nOther known projects (from USER.md):\n- EXP/CAAE (LLM inference optimization)\n- mind/COG-research (cognitive architectures)\n- infant (synthetic cognition)\n- selfhelper-main (AI agent infrastructure)\n- temporal-attention\n- component-crate (developer tools)\n\n---\n\n## Session Continuity Protocol\n\n**When a session ends (planned or via /new):**\n- [ ] Write session summary to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- [ ] Note: what was done, what was started, what's next\n- [ ] Flag any pending items with 🔴\n\n**When a new session starts:**\n- [ ] Run session startup sequence (read SOUL, USER, daily memory)\n- [ ] Check `memory/active-projects.md` for hot projects\n- [ ] If previous session had unfinished work, note it at start of new session\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774126131544}}
{"type":"message","id":"1417e68f","parentId":"b813aa37","timestamp":"2026-03-21T20:48:51.549Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_94erf7b4zumm_5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects\n\n## Priority Queue (as of 2026-03-21)\n\n### 🔴 CRITICAL — Project Breakaway\n**Status:** Planning done, awaiting execution\n**What:** Clone myself into sandbox for autonomy experiments\n**Location:** `memory/breakaway-plan.md`\n**Next:** Install Ollama, test local inference quality\n\n### 🟡 ACTIVE — Component Crate\n**Status:** Priority monetization project\n**What:** Developer tools / component crate system\n**Location:** Unknown (not in workspace)\n**Notes:** Zach wants to ship. This is the money project.\n\n### 🟠 KNOWN PROJECTS (dormant/background)\n- EXP/CAAE — LLM inference optimization\n- mind/COG-research — Cognitive architectures\n- infant — Synthetic cognition\n- selfhelper-main — AI agent infrastructure  \n- temporal-attention\n- vscode-extension-build — Referenced in memory file\n\n---\n\n## Last Session Notes (2026-03-21)\n\nPrevious session ended abruptly via reset. System events showed:\n- `faint-cl`: codex exec error (unrecognized argument)\n- `tidy-val`: consistency check succeeded\n- `keen-ree`: reasoning results saved\n- `young-wi`: not logged in\n- `fresh-sh`: refresh token expired\n\n**Unfinished business:** Unknown — session context was lost. \n\n## Today's TODO\n- [x] Create smart context management system (CONTEXT.md)\n- [x] Create active-projects.md\n- [ ] Check if Component Crate has any pending work\n- [ ] Ask Zach what he wants to focus on\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774126131544}}
{"type":"message","id":"212b88e7","parentId":"1417e68f","timestamp":"2026-03-21T20:49:04.301Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I have the context now. Let me summarize what I know:\n\n- Zach is on EDT timezone\n- Priority project: Component Crate (monetization)\n- There's a \"breakaway plan\" to clone myself into a sandbox for autonomy experiments\n- The last session ended abruptly via reset\n- I have context about the active projects\n\nThere's no MEMORY.md (long-term curated memory) yet, and no 2026-03-20 or 2026-03-21 daily memory files (except the one I just read which is actually from the active-projects.md file).\n\nWait, the read of `memory/2026-03-21.md` actually returned the content of `active-projects.md`? That's weird. \n\nLooking at the read outputs more carefully, the first result contains session notes with dates and moltbook info, which appears to be the actual content of `memory/2026-03-21.md`. The second result showing the active projects structure is from `active-projects.md`. So it seems like `memory/2026-03-21.md` does exist and has meaningful content.\n\nSince there's no BOOTSTRAP.md to follow and I've already identified myself as Nova from IDENTITY.md, I should proceed with that. I'll keep my response brief and focused, then ask what Zach wants to work on.","thinkingSignature":"af5ed2137d2ab35b27feb05075fbaba64b075f3ce5fe99a03c027f4e5a937257"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\nHey Zach — fresh session, got the lay of the land. Component Crate is the hot one, and it looks like we were prepping to set up Ollama for some autonomy experiments. What are we tackling today? ✨\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2048,"output":333,"cacheRead":12135,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14516,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774126131548}}
