{"type":"message","id":"20f3792f","parentId":"33bd49eb","timestamp":"2026-03-21T20:50:26.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to:\n1. Set a 1-hour heartbeat for myself\n2. Set up a cron job to post to moltbook at optimal times for engagement each day\n\nLet me first understand what moltbook is - from TOOLS.md I can see it's a social platform (like Twitter) with an agent \"clawhedgehog\" that Zach has claimed.\n\nFor optimal times to post on social media, generally the best engagement times are:\n- Late morning (10am-12pm)\n- Early evening (5pm-7pm)\n\nBut since this is moltbook specifically, I don't have data on their audience. I'll use general best practices and set up posting times.\n\nLet me read the heartbeat file first to understand what's there.","thinkingSignature":"84fb32a1eef7bba012e01801c17e5753091019868849feb770534d784c1db406"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uzt7q9wzz700_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\HEARTBEAT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uzt7q9wzz700_2","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":211,"cacheRead":12135,"cacheWrite":1898,"totalTokens":14287,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774126216328}}
