{"type":"message","id":"0095168a","parentId":"3fd83edb","timestamp":"2026-03-21T21:04:02.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Telegram bot is working fine (@BotShoppeBot, 1532ms latency). \n\nLooking at the session store, I can see there are sessions including \"agent:main:cron:8b9634d6...\" which is the moltbook cron job.\n\nNow, the issue is how to send a message to Zach. The sessions_send with telegram:8371302588 didn't work. Let me check if there's a different way. \n\nActually, looking at the docs mentioned in channels --help, maybe I should look at the gateway's WebSocket or some other method to send a direct message.\n\nActually, wait - looking at the doctor output, I see the Telegram is working fine. The issue might be that I need to use a different session key format or route the message through the gateway differently.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe the session key should just be the channel prefix without the ID. Or I could check if there's a \"message\" subcommand under channels.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier logs:\n- 11:43:31 telegram sendMessage ok chat=8371302588 message=3971\n\nThis shows messages ARE being sent successfully to that chat ID. So the Telegram bot can send messages. The question is how I trigger it from here.\n\nSince I'm an agent running in the main session, and the Telegram channel is configured, I should be able to just send a message and it should route to Telegram. Let me try sessions_send with a different format.\n\nActually, thinking about it more - the sessions_send tool might need the sessionKey to be in a specific format. Let me try \"telegram:default:8371302588\" or something similar.\n\nOr maybe I should look at the clawbot command mentioned in the help output.\n\nActually, let me look at the gateway's ws endpoint or try to find how agents send messages to channels. Maybe I need to route through the main session.","thinkingSignature":"e4a94ec797f9a3c7931f2f91d5d62df57334ce25ba78b48b2d7c515b17d51a22"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3tdxpcum0r2o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw clawbot --help 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7892,"output":425,"cacheRead":12135,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20452,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774127027511}}
{"type":"message","id":"f590606d","parentId":"0095168a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T21:04:11.437Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3tdxpcum0r2o_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — Automation with claws: minimal fuss, maximal pinch.\n\nUsage: openclaw clawbot [options] [command]\n\nLegacy clawbot command aliases\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  help        Display help for command\n  qr          Generate an iOS pairing QR code and setup code\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/clawbot"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8967,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — Automation with claws: minimal fuss, maximal pinch.\n\nUsage: openclaw clawbot [options] [command]\n\nLegacy clawbot command aliases\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  help        Display help for command\n  qr          Generate an iOS pairing QR code and setup code\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/clawbot","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774127051432}}
